The naga folder contains elements to wrap the carma of compass project with python.


In order to compile, environment variable required:
    path to compass: COMPASS_ROOT 
    path to cuda   : CUDA_ROOT

REQUIREMENT:
    * cython 0.22
    * python 2.7
    * carma librairie

The compilation is done with the command:
    python setup.py build_ext --inplace

To clean the folder, use the command:
    python clean.py

The module can be tested using (in the naga/ folder):
    nosetests test/*.py
failure should only triggered by precision issues


Content
    * wrapper sources:
            naga.pxd
            naga.pyx
            naga_context.pyx
            naga_obj.pyx.in
            naga_host_obj.pyx.in
            naga_magma.pyx.in
            naga_streams.pyx
            naga_timer.pyx
    * process_tmpl.py             template management
    * setup.py                    compilation setups
    * clean.py                    cleaning script
    * test                        directory containing small python test codes
